b'$TSLA $TSLA can someone explain the price action ? Is it sustainable? It\xe2\x80\x99s severely overvalued. Has it ever happened before with any stock ? Will it crash?'

b'$TSLA Friday's price action was somewhat suspicious. Premarket activity pegged this around 565 and continued to decline until there was a burst of volume in the premarket that kept it from falling after the NHTSA investigation news.

Runs up based on green open# and steadily decays for the remainder of the session# a bear market indicator at least on the daily end. 

Further# a put I used as a hedge suddenly gapped up to breakeven on the day in the last 30 minutes of trading.

If I had to guess# that investigation news isn't being ignored by institutions and some wealthier holders are looking to exit their position and hedge with puts in case of liquidity issues.'
